All aluminum frames shall be pre-assembled at factory incorporating welded construction for all joints. Frames and grilles shall be shipped fully assembled in protective wooden crating to each jobsite. For sections larger than 6' 0 by 8' 0 a mechanical joint is to be provided (if specified). A silicone joint is to be applied between the frame and the finished floor to prevent any water infiltration (by others).

Features

It all starts at the core. xcore connect™ advances the science of vinyl flooring through the use of a patented core technology that is inherently stable and dent resistant. The flexible lightweight concrete, fiber-reinforced composition eliminates concerns about unsightly gaps between boards and is engineered with extreme durability to accommodate high traffic commercial environments.

• Authentic Look: Attractive, natural-looking wood and stone designs in grand format planks and tiles
• Dimensionally Stable: The flexible lightweight concrete core is fiber-reinforced and delivers 5x greater dimensional stability than traditional LVT.
• Sunlight Stable: xcore connect™ is the only floating vinyl flooring solution to withstand direct sunlight and temperatures over 120° F.
• Dent Resistant: Withstands high impact to avoid holes, gouges and indentations.
• Built-in Sound Reduction: Backing serves as an attached underlayment for built-in sound reduction and a warmer floor.
• Easy Installation: No additional underlayment, no adhesive and the hybrid structure prevents telegraphing of minor subfloor imperfections.

Common Uses
Corporate offices, hospitality, multi-family, retail.

CleanZone™
Zone 4: Interior

Warranty
10 Year Limited

Specifications

Material
New category of flooring with a hybrid compound structure consisting of xcore connect™ patented core technology with an acoustic EVA backing, decorative layer, PU protective layer and XTRA-DUR top coating.

Format

Features

The Tailor Grace collections feature contemporary designs, wood and stone looks with useful properties including matte finish, sound reduction, indentation resistance and comfort underfoot. A commercial-grade, heterogeneous smooth sheet vinyl with a comfort or acoustic backing. Manufactured from PVC with glass fiber reinforcement scrim between the print film and backing. The 3.9mm product has a blown PVC backing, while the 2.85mm has a slightly blown PVC with a fleece added to enhance the bonding.

100% phthalate-free resilient vinyl flooring manufactured with water based inks and no heavy metals in an ISO 9001 and 14001 certified facility. Tailor Grace does not require waxing, buffing or stripping, and maintenance requirements are simple and will not negatively impact indoor air quality, energy consumption or facility costs making it the optimal flooring for environments where hygiene and minimal downtime are priorities.

name: Formative Clic
short_description:
Formative Clic is inspired by the beauty and design of natural hardwood floors. Formative Clic offers all of the refinement of authentic wood planks combined with the benefits of resilient flooring. Formative Clic features:

  • Easy installation: Formative Clic planks click together easily with an edge-locking system for a glue-less installation that saves labor time and money.
  • Quick shipping: Heavy inventory levels available in the US provide for immediate delivery, allowing tight timelines to be met.
  • Acoustic backing: The acoustic backing dampens sound transmission with an IIC value of 61 (ASTM E492), creating a quieter and more comfortable environment.
